# BirdieIQ documentation checkpoints

When editing files under `docs/`:

- Work checkpoints in order (CP-0 → CP-1 → …). See [docs/CONVENTIONS.md](docs/CONVENTIONS.md).
- Each completed checkpoint gets a journal: `docs/journal/CP-XX.md` using `_TEMPLATE.md` task format (Recommendation / Why / Alternatives / Risks / Next action).
- Update [docs/specs/00-INDEX.md](docs/specs/00-INDEX.md) and [docs/PROJECT_STATUS.md](docs/PROJECT_STATUS.md) when a spec is completed.
- Major technical choices go in [docs/DECISIONS.md](docs/DECISIONS.md) as ADRs.

Do not mark a checkpoint complete without meeting exit criteria in the workplan.
